name: Vegan Gluten-Free Dumplings
author: MyNutriCounter
summary: Rice paper is a low-calorie, gluten-free option in comparison to wheat-based products. This delicate, translucent vegan dumpling allows the diner to see the colorful nutritious vegetables, which are bursting with vitamins. Another serving option is to create a rice wrap by leaving one end open, allowing the vegetables to cascade onto the plate creating a delicious display.
ingredients: 1 teaspoon sesame oil, or as needed
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon sesame oil, tamari, hot water, and chia seeds in a small bowl
Combine bloomed chia seed mixture with mushrooms, carrots, shallot, leeks, ginger, Chinese five-spice powder, and pepper in a bowl
Fill a large, shallow container with cold water
Soak rice paper, 1 at a time, until pliable, about 10 seconds
Lay softened rice paper on a plate, rough side up
Scoop a heaping tablespoon of filling near an edge of the rice paper
Fold left and right edges in toward the center, then fold top and bottom edges in to create a large dumpling
Repeat with remaining rice paper and filling
Place a steamer insert into a saucepan and fill with water to just below the bottom of the steamer
Brush remaining sesame oil onto the insert to keep dumplings from sticking
Add dumplings, cover, and steam until tender, about 3 minutes
